        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:24PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 224 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Highland Park, or 35 miles southwest of Denver, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Evergreen, Harris Park, Pine Junction, Highland Park and Shaffers
Crossing.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
